From 965b9d9f4890c5df26dab413200c812ea3ed5ade Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ASK2 PR14c-prep <ask2@vyos.local>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 03:13:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman/pcd: Coarse Classifier public API stub (PR14c-prep)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

PR14c-prep of the ASK2 v1.0 PR14 series. Adds the Coarse Classifier
(CC) public ABI surface and a fman_pcd_cc.c translation unit that
provides -EOPNOTSUPP / ERR_PTR(-EOPNOTSUPP) stubs for every entry
point. PR14c-body will replace the stubs with real silicon-resident
tree/node programming per LS1046A RM 8.7.4.1-8.7.4.3.

Two-step landing pattern proven on PR14b:
  PR14c-prep (this commit) — public ABI + Makefile + stubs, builds clean
  PR14c-body — real implementation, byte-perfect against RM tables

New public types in <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h>:
  - enum fman_pcd_action_type      (6 variants: DROP, FORWARD_FQ,
                                    FORWARD_CAAM, REPLICATE, MANIPULATE,
                                    NEXT_CC_NODE) — single discriminator
                                    replacing the SDK's 16 separate
                                    t_FmPcdCcNextEngineParams flavors
  - struct fman_pcd_action         (tagged union)
  - enum fman_pcd_cc_extract_type  (KEY / HDR / NONHDR per RM 8.7.4.2)
  - struct fman_pcd_cc_extract
  - struct fman_pcd_cc_key_entry   (56-byte key+mask + action)
  - struct fman_pcd_cc_key_table

New public functions (all stubbed):
  - fman_pcd_cc_tree_create        — allocate match-tree
  - fman_pcd_cc_node_create        — allocate node with extract+keys
  - fman_pcd_cc_node_add_key       — append one key+action pair
  - fman_pcd_cc_node_modify_next_action — replace action atomically
  - fman_pcd_cc_node_destroy
  - fman_pcd_cc_tree_destroy

Wiring:
  drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/Makefile — fman_pcd_cc.o added
  to fsl_dpaa_fman-$(CONFIG_FSL_FMAN_PCD).  fman_pcd.c already exports
  fman_pcd_get_cc_list() and the cc_trees list (landed in PR14a).

Provenance (v1.1) per spec §16: authored from LS1046A RM only.
The legacy NXP SDK fm_cc.c (~7500 LOC in archived
mihakralj/kernel-ls1046a-build@464df181) is read-only cross-reference;
no code or struct layouts copied.

Validation (native ARM64 build on Cobalt 100):
  - make ARCH=arm64 -j32 Image  → success, zero warnings
  - System.map: all 6 fman_pcd_cc_* symbols present as 'T', each with
    matching __ksymtab_fman_pcd_cc_* entry
  - No regression in any other translation unit

References:
  specs/ask2-rewrite-spec.md §13.3 (fman_pcd_cc.c, ~2500 LOC budget)
  specs/ask2-rewrite-spec.md §16  (provenance discipline risk #12)
  LS1046A Reference Manual §8.7.4.1, §8.7.4.2, §8.7.4.3

Signed-off-by: ASK2 PR14c-prep <ask2@vyos.local>
